org.eclipse.dirigible.core.git

Interface IGitConnector

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    GitConnector

    public interface IGitConnector
    The IGitConnector provides the simplified methods for communicating with a Git SCM server.

      • add

        void add(String filePattern)
  throws IOException,
         org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.NoFilepatternException,
         org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.GitAPIException
        Adds content from file(s) to the staging index.
        Parameters:
        filePattern - File to add content from. Example: "." includes all files. If "dir/subdir/" is directory then "dir/subdir" all files from the directory recursively
        Throws:
        IOException - IO Exception
        org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.NoFilepatternException - No File Pattern Exception
        org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.GitAPIException - Git API Exception

      • commit

        void commit(String message,
            String name,
            String email,
            boolean all)
     throws org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.NoHeadException,
            org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.NoMessageException,
            org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.UnmergedPathsException,
            org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.ConcurrentRefUpdateException,
            org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.WrongRepositoryStateException,
            org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.GitAPIException,
            IOException
        Adds changes to the staging index. Then makes commit.
        Parameters:
        message - the commit message
        name - the name of the committer used for the commit
        email - the email of the committer used for the commit
        all - if set to true, command will automatically stages files that have been modified and deleted, but new files not known by the repository are not affected. This corresponds to the parameter -a on the command line.
        Throws:
        org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.NoHeadException - No Head Exception
        org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.NoMessageException - No Message Exception
        org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.UnmergedPathsException - Unmerged Path Exception
        org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.ConcurrentRefUpdateException - Concurrent Ref Update Exception
        org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.WrongRepositoryStateException - Wrong Repository State Exception
        org.eclipse.jgit.api.errors.GitAPIException - Git API Exception
        IOException - IO Exception
